                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14347474" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2015 20:00:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Possible fix: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mduerig/jackrabbit-oak/commit/f9e2092421f671a553f9979e8d33a4afe9680bef&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mduerig/jackrabbit-oak/commit/f9e2092421f671a553f9979e8d33a4afe9680bef&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only register a single &lt;tt&gt;GCMonitor&lt;/tt&gt; per repository that delegates to per session &lt;tt&gt;GCMonitor&lt;/tt&gt; instances. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14347483" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2015 20:06:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On a more general note I find that hidden contract of &lt;tt&gt;Whiteboard#register&lt;/tt&gt; not being able to cope with many (un)registrations disturbing. (How much is &apos;many&apos; anyway?). This is even more problematic as &apos;many&apos; is implementation dependent and the problem doesn&apos;t show up in any of the tests/ITs/benchmarks we have in Oak. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14347486" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2015 20:08:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BTW, this will also affect 1.1.7 once the ongoing vote passed. I thus set the fix version to include 1.1.8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14348484" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2015 09:38:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix looks good and I applied it to trunk: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1664184&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1664184&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Merged to 1.0 branch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1664291&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1664291&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14502847" author="edivad" created="Mon, 20 Apr 2015 13:45:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 1.0.13&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
